This paper discusses a software requirements intelligence service that collects, processes, analyzes, and visualizes user feedback. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) as it deals with software development and requirements. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of social media and app stores, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the challenges of manual analysis, which could fall under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper mentions the use of analytics and visualization, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
